# kaggle base.manifest — kaggle's module declaration for the weave layer compiler.
#
# kaggle is the platform-integration SUBSTRATE layer: it consumes metis (construct/deps
# `substrate ../metis`, transitively ariadne) and is itself consumed by kbench. It
# inherits the EXPORTED base layer through that edge, and will EXPORT its own Kaggle
# step-types (download, submit) + Competition/Submission/Leaderboard tooling downstream
# via `export` rows added as those land (kaggle-ml-base-layer, kaggle#1). For now it
# declares only its OWN internal constitution.
#
# Format and verbs: see ariadne's construct/base.manifest. The leading `internal`
# token (ariadne#99) keeps an artifact with this repo (selected only on its own
# self-walk); an ancestor's internal artifacts never leak DOWN into a consumer's
# composed AGENTS.md (the #95 fix). NOTE: shipping a base.manifest is ALSO what marks
# kaggle as a TRAVERSABLE layer — without it, kbench's weave walk stops at kaggle.

# ── Constitution ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
internal  prose AGENTS.local.md
